==Notable Russian Muslims==

* Khabib Nurmagomedov is a former professional mixed martial artist.
*Abdulmanap Nurmagomedov, Soviet military veteran, former judoka and combat sports coach, and the father of former UFC Undisputed Lightweight Champion Khabib Nurmagomedov
* Islam Makhachev is a professional mixed martial artist and current UFC undisputed lightweight champion. 
* Usman Nurmagomedov is a professional mixed martial artist and current Bellator MMA undisputed lightweight champion
* Umar Nurmagomedov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Magomed Ankalaev is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Zabit Magomedsharipov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Tagir Ulanbekov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Ikram Aliskerov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Abubakar Nurmagomedov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Gadzhi Rabadanov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Saygid Izagakhmaev is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Zubaira Tukhugov is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Rudolf Nureyev was considered the greatest male ballet dancer of his generation.
* Marat Safin a former world No. 1 tennis player.
* Vyacheslav Polosin was a former Russian Orthodox Church priest who was at the forefront of a campaign to make Orthodox Christmas a public holiday in Russia and converted to Islam in 1999.
* Alina Zagitova is a figure skater.
* Shamil Musaev is a freestyle wrestler.
* Movlid Khaybulaev is a professional mixed martial artist.
* Movsar Evloev is a mixed martial artist, who is currently competing in the featherweight division of the UFC. A professional since 2014, he has also competed at 1 Global, where he is the former bantamweight.
* Imam Shamil was a political leader and Imam of Dagestan, who resisted against Russian expansion of the Caucasus.
* Ramazan Ramazanov is a kickboxer.
* Alisher Usmanov, oligarch
* Elvira Nabiullina, head of Russia state bank

