<doc id="1184514" wikidata="Q10296131" url="?curid=1184514" title="Mojo Records">
<text>Mojo Records was a California-based record label founded in 1995 by producer Jay Rifkin. It became a joint venture with Universal Records in 1996 and then sold to the Zomba Group in 2001, who placed it under their subsidiary Jive Records. The label has been largely inactive since Zomba was purchased and restructured under BMG in 2003, save for a few reissues of older material. The final releases from the label were Reel Big Fish&#x27;s &quot;We&#x27;re Not Happy &#x27;til You&#x27;re Not Happy&quot; and Goldfinger&#x27;s &quot;The Best of Goldfinger&quot; in early 2005.

